								<div id="comment-18142" class="a_comment">
				<p>This post is not properly worded. Displax skin is not a "display" as stated: "can turn virtually any surface into a multi-touch display." IT should read "multi-touch surface." Huge Difference.</p>
<p></p>
<p>It is merely a touch-sensitive (and wind sensitive) film which can be placed over other materials. </p>
<p></p>
<p>The Displax site even says the material is completely transparent so it does not interfere with the display behind - hence, no display properties/capabilities inherent in the material.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Pretty useless unless it's paired with a display of some sort, or coupled with other new techology that has not yet proliferated consumer markets.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
